# ThreadSanitizer suppression file for FalkorDB tests
#
# This file suppresses known false positives reported by ThreadSanitizer (TSAN)
# when running FalkorDB tests against a TSAN-instrumented Redis server.
#
# Suppressions follow the format:
#   race:<function_or_symbol>
#
# Common false positives from Redis internals and OS primitives:

# epoll_wait is a kernel syscall — any apparent "race" on it is a TSAN
# instrumentation artifact, not a real data race.
race:epoll_wait

# Redis event-loop processing; aeProcessEvents accesses event state that is
# protected by the single-threaded event loop model but TSAN cannot infer that.
race:aeProcessEvents

# Redis background I/O thread (BIO) performs disk/close operations; accesses
# to the job queue are serialised by Redis but TSAN may flag them.
race:bioProcessBackgroundJobs
